oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Bullets and a sash buckle
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Shadow box containing 2 bullets and a sash buckle with a flower stamped on it. One of the bullets is a .73 caliber and the other is a C.S. Gardner with an insert. The sash buckle is a C.S. sash buckle with a flower stamped in the metal. The bullets were excavated at Plantation Inn and the sash buckle was unearthed on Leatherwood Road.
